{"body": "T P -1. D. A-V (2025-12) 1 of 2\n\nAmount for Dependants and Amount Transferred\nby a Child Pursuing Studies\nA\n\nT\n\nSCHEDULE\n\nA\n\nAmount for a child under 18 enrolled in post-secondary studies (see line 367 in the guide)\n\nIf the child was born after December 31, 2007, and in 2025 was a full-time student pursuing vocational training at the secondary level\nor post-secondary studies, complete the table below.\nIf you are claiming an amount for more than three children, attach a sheet containing the required information and carry the result of your calculations\nto line 22.\nIf you are splitting the amount for a child under 18 enrolled in post-secondary studies with another person,\nenter their social insurance number. \b�����������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n1\nChild’s last name\nFirst name\nSocial insurance number\nDate of birth (YYYY MM DD)\nRelationship to you\nAmount for post-secondary studies,\nRL-8 slip, box A (maximum $7,646)\nDependent child’s income\nAmount from line 275 of the child’s return\nAmount from line 236 of the child’s return\nAdd lines 10 and 12.\nScholarships, bursaries or any similar financial\nassistance reported on line 154 of the child’s return\nSubtract line 16 from line 14.\nIf the result is negative, enter 0.\nSubtract line 18 from line 7.\nIf the result is negative, enter 0.\n\n2\n\n3\n\n2\n3\n4\n5\n6\n7\n10\n\n+ 12\n= 14\n– 16\n= 18\n21\n\nAdd all the amounts on line 21.\nCarry the result to line 367 of your return.\b\n\nB\n\nSocial insurance number\n1\n\nAmount for a child under 18 enrolled in post-secondary studies\n\n22\n\nAmount transferred by a child 18 or over enrolled in post-secondary studies (see line 367 in the guide)\n\nA child born before January 1, 2008, who in 2025 was a full-time student pursuing vocational training at the secondary level or post-secondary\nstudies can transfer the unused portion of the basic tax credit to their father or mother (as a recognized parental contribution). The child must file\nan income tax return and complete Schedule S to calculate the amount they can transfer and to designate the recipient(s) of the transfer.\nIf a child is transferring an amount to you, complete the table below.\nIf more than three children are transferring an amount to you, attach a sheet containing the required information and carry the result\nof your calculations to line 29.\n1\nChild’s last name\nFirst name\nSocial insurance number\nDate of birth (YYYY MM DD)\nRelationship to you\nAmount transferred to you by the child\n(lines 20.1 and 20.2 of the child’s Schedule S)\n\n2\n\n3\n\n23\n24\n25\n26\n27\n\n28\n\nAdd all the amounts on line 28. Carry the result to line 367 of your return.\n\b\nAmount transferred by a child 18 or over enrolled in post-secondary studies\n\nY4A1 ZZ 89526549\n\n29\n\nA\n\nT\n\nC\n\nT P -1. D. A-V (2025-12) 2 of 2\n\nAmount for other dependants (see line 367 in the guide)\n\nComplete the table below only if your dependants were born before January 1, 2008.\nIf you are claiming an amount for more than two dependants, attach a sheet containing the required information and carry the result\nof your calculations to line 56.\nNOTE\nYou cannot claim an amount for your spouse or for a child who is transferring, in their 2025 return, an amount as a child 18 or over enrolled\nin post-secondary studies.\n\nIf you are splitting the amount for other dependants with another person,\nenter their social insurance number. \b�����������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n\nSocial insurance number\n30\n\n1\nDependant’s last name\nFirst name\nSocial insurance number\nDate of birth (YYYY MM DD)\nRelationship to you\n\n31\n\nBasic amount\nReduction of the amount for other dependants if the dependant turned 18 in 2025\n(see the guide)\nSubtract line 40 from line 37.\n\n37\n\n32\n33\n34\n35\n\nDependant’s income\nAmount from line 275 of the dependant’s return\nAmount from line 236 of the dependant’s return\n\n5,570 00\n\n5,570 00\n\n– 40\n= 41\n42\n\n+ 44\n= 46\n\nAdd lines 42 and 44.\nScholarships, bursaries or any similar financial assistance\nreported on line 154 of the dependant’s return\nSubtract line 48 from line 46.\nIf the result is negative, enter 0.\n\n– 48\n= 50\n\nSubtract line 50 from line 41.\nIf the result is negative, enter 0.\n\n54\n\nAdd all the amounts on line 54.\nCarry the result to line 367 of your return. \b\n\nD\n\n2\n\nAmount for other dependants\n\n56\n\nTax credit for tuition or examination fees transferred by a child\n\nA student can transfer the unused portion of the tax credit for tuition or examination fees paid for the year to one of their or their spouse’s parents\nor grandparents.\nThe child must file an income tax return and complete Schedule T to calculate the amount they can transfer and to designate the recipient\nof the transfer.\nIf a child is transferring an amount to you, complete the table below.\nIf more than three children are transferring an amount to you, attach a sheet containing the required information and carry the result\nof your calculations to line 70.\n1\nChild’s last name\nFirst name\nSocial insurance number\nDate of birth (YYYY MM DD)\nRelationship to you\nAmount transferred to you by the child\n(line 68 of the child’s Schedule T)\n\n2\n\n60\n61\n62\n63\n64\n65\n\nAdd all the amounts on line 65. Carry the result to line 398.1 of your return.\n\b\nTax credit for tuition or examination fees transferred by a child\nEnclose this schedule with your return.\nIf you want to keep a copy for your records, see the guide.\n\n3\n\nY4A2 ZZ 89526550\n\n70\n\nA", "citation_label": "Revenu Quebec Schedule A 2025 - Amount for Dependants and Amount Transferred by a Child", "citation_path": "ca/policy/revenu-quebec/tp1-2025/schedule-a-dependants", "document_class": "policy", "expression_date": "2025-01-01", "heading": "Revenu Quebec Schedule A 2025 - Amount for Dependants and Amount Transferred by a Child", "id": "99bcc8c3-c564-5c08-af82-ee5ef60c10a3", "jurisdiction": "ca", "kind": "document", "language": "en", "level": 1, "metadata": {"content_type": "application/pdf", "discovered_via": "manual-review:canada-2026-tax-encode", "document_subtype": "revenu_quebec_schedule", "primary_source": true, "program": "tp1_2025_schedule_a_dependants", "source_authority": "Revenu Quebec", "source_discovery_group": "ca/policy/tax", "title": "Revenu Quebec Schedule A 2025 - Amount for Dependants and Amount Transferred by a Child"}, "ordinal": 1, "source_as_of": "2026-07-03", "source_format": "text", "source_id": "revenu-quebec-2025-schedule-a-dependants", "source_path": "sources/ca/policy/2026-07-03-revenu-quebec-2025-schedule-a-dependants/official-documents/tp-1-d-a-v-2025.txt", "source_url": "https://www.revenuquebec.ca/documents/en/formulaires/tp/2025-12/TP-1.D.A-V%282025-12%29.pdf", "version": "2026-07-03-revenu-quebec-2025-schedule-a-dependants"}
